That part which until 1.4.1931 formed the parish of Kinson. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Kinson. Abolished 9.11.1905 
    and added to the parish of Poole.

Abolished 1.4.1933 and divided between the parishes of Poole and 
    Pamphill. See also Table 2, notes (a), (b) and (d).

Created 1.2.1986 by renaming the parish of Hampreston. See 
    also Table 2, note (i).

Renamed 1.2.1986 to become the parish of Ferndown Town. See also Table 2, note 
    (f).
Abolished 9.11.1905 and added to the parish of Poole.

Abolished 1.4.1931 and added to the parish of Bournemouth. 
    See also Table 2, notes (b) and (c).
Abolished 9.11.1905 and added to the parish of Poole.

Renamed 19.8.1986 to become the parish of Lytchett Minster & 
    Upton.

Created 19.8.1986 by renaming the parish of Lytchett Minster. See 
    also Table 2, note (j).

Name changed to Milborne St. Andrew by 1974. See also Table 2, notes 
    (f) and (g).
Abolished 9.11.1905 and added to the parish of Poole.

Created 9.11.1905 out of the parishes of Branksome, Parkstone, 
    Poole St. James, Longfleet and Hamworthy. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished 
    area.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish  of Poole. 
    Abolished 1.4.2019 and added to the Bournemouth, Christchurch & Poole 
    unparished area. See also Table 2, note (k).
Abolished 9.11.1905 and added to the parish of Poole.

Renamed 18.10.1984 to become the parish of Wareham Town. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

Created 18.10.1984 by renaming the parish of Wareham Lady St. 
    Mary. See also Table 2, note (j).
